prompt: If NTPPi(x,y) and NTPP(y,z) then what are the possible relationships between x and z?
answer:
### Answer:
EQ(x,z), PO(x,z), TPP(x,z), TPPi(x,z), NTPP(x,z), NTPPi(x,z)

The possible relationships between x and z are EQ (coincident), PO (partial overlap), TPP (tangential proper part), TPPi (inverse tangential proper part), NTPP (non-tangential proper part), and NTPPi (inverse non-tangential proper part). Since y is a common non-tangential proper part of both x and z, x and z must overlap at least in y, ruling out DC (disconnected) and EC (externally connected). The remaining relations are all feasible depending on how x and z are positioned relative to each other while containing y.
